Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Children and Youth Services Coordinator Bowen Island , BC Description Are you passionate about fostering a love for books, learning, and community? The Bowen Island Public Library is seeking a Children and Youth Services Coordinator to lead our programs and services for young readers and their families for the next two years.About the Role As a key member of our team, you will design and deliver engaging programs, curate vibrant collections, and build meaningful community connections. Reporting to the Chief Librarian, you will also provide leadership to staff and volunteers while delivering excellent customer service and ensuring smooth daily operations. Full job description is online.
QualificationsPost-secondary degree or diploma in a related field (Master’s in Library Science or Library Technician Diploma preferred). Minimum 2 years’ experience in related work plus minimum 1 year in a leadership role. Experience with collection development and cataloging. Enthusiasm for community engagement and outreach.Why Join Us?Be part of a vibrant library that values equity, creativity, and service excellence.Work in a beautiful island setting with a supportive and collaborative team.Make a meaningful impact on the lives of children, youth, and families.DetailsSee full job description on our websiteCompensation $33.43 to $42.33 per hour commensurate with qualifications.20 hours per week. Includes weekend and evening hours.Two year temporary contract position through to December 31, 2026How to ApplyInterested candidates should apply by email, with cover letter and resume attached as one document to Tina Nielsen at info@bowenlibrary.ca. Use Children’s Coordinator Position in the subject line. Closing date Friday January 24, 2025. Compensation $33.43 to $42.33 per hour. Commensurate with qualifications. Closes: 24 January, 2025 Bowen Island Public Library Bowen Island , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
