to the community beyond the traditional notions of a library. Through the Chief Librarian &amp; CEO, Vancouver Public Library plays a key role in ensuring a healthy, resilient and sustainable community. The ideal candidate brings senior level management experience in a complex, unionized, urban library system. Alternatively, they may be a CEO in a complex, multi-partner, multi-unit unionized environment with parallels to a municipal library. The ability to implement a vision, manage a complex budget, and lead a passionate and distributed team is required. The role is ideally suited to leaders with a strong commitment to VPL’s values and who can cultivate positive and effective working relationships with a wide variety of internal and external partners including the Board, City, staff, union, VPL Foundation and other partners. Based in Vancouver, BC, this role is perfect for a visionary and transformative library services leader to take on a pivotal role in an institution that helps its community by connecting people to each other and to ideas. In accordance with BC’s Pay Transparency Act, the salary range for the role is $240,000 to $316,297 with a targeted mid-point of ($272,100).The salary offered to the successful candidate will consider a wide array of factors including but not limited to the individual’s skillset, level of experience applicable to the role they are being offered and internal equity considerations. To explore this opportunity further, please click ‘apply’. We thank all applicants for their interest in this position. Please note that we will only be in contact with those individuals moving forward with our client. The Vancouver Public Library acknowledges that it is situated on the ancestral, unceded, and traditional territories of the xʷməθkʷəy̓əm (Musqueam), Sḵwx̱wú7mesh (Squamish), and səlilwətaɬ (Tsleil-Waututh) Nations. Compensation $240,000 to $316,297 Closes: 19 March, 2025 Vancouver Public Library Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use 