s; performs collection inventory.Ensures intercampus/interlibrary loan requests for print and media are processed efficiently using automated systems, following established policies and procedures.Provides reference and research assistance.Assists Customers with library catalogue, database and internet searching.Collects, compiles and submits campus and college wide library statistics monthly and annually.Participates in projects such as evaluating reference databases and formulating library procedures.Provides input into the development, design, and content of library forms.Monitors and distributes incoming library materials to students from partner institutions.Troubleshoots problems with equipment such as computers, and multi-function printersAdvises the Coordinator of Library Services on campus library capital requests.Performs other library duties, as required.REQUIRED EDUCATION &amp; EXPERIENCELibrary Technician diplomaMinimum of 2 years recent public services experience in an automated library.REQUIRED KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS &amp; ABILITIESFamiliarity with BC post-secondary library initiatives; resource-sharing consortia and networksBasic level of proficiency with MS Office including Word and Excel. Demonstrated familiarity with and proficiency in the use of journal databases and e-resourcesExcellent communication, interpersonal and customer service skills, with demonstrated ability to exercise tact, good judgment and diplomacy.Excellent organizational and time management skills, with the ability to plan and prioritize tasks, ensure attention to detail and efficiently meet deadlines.Demonstrated ability in effective team behaviors such as active listening, sharing, balanced participation, and development of shared team goals.Ability to perform functional supervisory role at a campus library level.Ability to work independently, display initiative, and apply effective analytical thinking to solve problems.Ability to adapt to change with a positive attitude, demonstrating flexibility and effectiveness.Apply to: https://careers.nic.bc.ca/postings/6459 Compensation $30.44 - $32.30 per hour Closes: 11 March, 2025 North Island College Courtenay , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
